Fungus Trunk Polyporales Mushroom Bryophyte Moss Medicinal mushroom Inonotus Agaricomycetes Old-growth forest
Date: 2024-05-31 19:29:17
Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espécie é um saprófito ou parasita específico de espécies do género Betula. Pode observar-se em troncos e ramos, árvores mortas, mas por vezes também em espécimes vivos, provavelmente aproveitando árvores já em mau estado fitossanitário em que a infeção é mais fácil de propagar. Como outros fungos de podridão castanha degrada a parte dos hidratos de carbono(celulose) da lignocelulose, deixando a lignina na forma de fragmentos cúbicos castanhos, em contraste com os fungos de podridão branca que degradam na forma oposta. Em Portugal só encontrei esta espécie em habitats de altitude em serras. Serra da Arada 05/2024 #fomitopsisbetulina #birchpolypore #fomitopsis #fomitopsidaceae #polyporales #polyporaceae #betula #betulapubescens #betulaceltiberica #agaricomycetes #basidiomycota #polypore #fungi #fungus #fungos #fungiphotography #fungiidentification #mushroomidentification #mushroom #mushrooms #mushroomhunting #mushroomphotography #mycophotography #mycology #micologia #cogumelos #cogumelo #wildlifephotography #wildlifephotography

Orange Fungus Mushroom Science Graphic design
Date: 2023-09-27 22:52:50
Caption: 29 de setembro, às 18h Aula de Cultivo de Cogumelos Psicogênicos e o Impacto na Qualidade do Produto Final Sobre o professor: Rafael é bacharel em Ciências Biológicas pela UNESP, responsável técnico e fundador da empresa Fungicultura, pioneira no Brasil em vendas de cultura líquida de espécies de cogumelos comestíveis e medicinais. Na aula abordaremos: - Breve história do cultivo de cogumelos; - Espécies de Psilocybe; - Ciclo de vida; - Métodos de cultivo (esporos, clonagem, ágar, cultura líquida, spawn, casing, cultivo outdoor etc.); - Strains e potência; - Colheita, desidratação e armazenamento. Atenção: Atualmente cultivar e vender cogumelos mágicos é proibido no Brasil. Aula com fins educacionais. Garanta sua inscrição! LINK NA BIO #psicodelico #fungicultura #cultivo #cogumelos #cogumelosmagicos #psilocybecubensis #psilocybe #psychedelic

Date: 2024-02-11 05:11:30
Caption: It’s always a delight to find a pop of color in the woods during the winter months. 🧡 The fruiting bodies of the mock oyster are a lovely sherbet orange with fuzzy caps and crowded gills. They drop a very pale pink spore print, so be sure when conducting a print to use white paper. Most people say they stink, but I’ve never experienced that when finding these. They can be found growing in clustered rows on dead hardwood trees, but can also be found on conifers. 🆔: Phyllotopsis nidulans | mock oyster . . . #mycology #mycologymonday #foragervibes #mockoyster #wintermushrooms #phyllotopsis #phyllotopsisnidulans #nidulariaceae #fungikingdom #fungihunting #fungiphoto #fungiofinstagram #fantasticfungi #planetfungi #mushrooms_of_our_world #oklahomamushrooms

Caption: This structure caught my attention as it harmonizes with nature, so I stopped to take a picture of it. I originally thought this was a coffee shop in the middle of a mountain road, away from houses but right in front of a temple. It’s just naturally beautiful in every angle. Later, I found out that it was a wood-ear beverage and sausage shop. The owners were so hospitable and kind to show us their fruiting room. They cultivate the mushroom by themselves and process it into a beverage.  I like wood-ear beverages because they are healthy. Also, it contains substances which are good for our overall health. So I bought three bottles. Besides the beverage, I bought the pink mushroom, which tasted so good when cooked with ginger and seasoned with soy sauce.  #miaoli #miaolitravel #miaolifood #woodearmushrooms #woodear #fungicultura #fungiculture #taiwantravels #taiwanmountain #mountainview #natureshots

Book Paper Publication Paper Product Book cover Notebook Carnivorous plant Handwriting Wildflower Ink Magic Mushroom Cultivation Fungi Mycologist
Date: 2023-12-26 08:09:47
Caption: "Magic Mushroom Cultivation” by Steven Pollock M.D. (1977) is one of the legendary texts in the cultivation of "magic mushrooms". Many popular books were published in the US during the 70’s about the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., but this one stands out as one of the better known, particularly because in time Pollock was (incorrectly) associated with the cubensis strain "P envy". Pollock is also well known for finding and cultivating P. tampanensis, aka "Philosophers Stones". Psilocybe cubensis is one of the most cultivated mushrooms, and as a consequence of extensive collection, cultivation, breeding, and marketing ploys by various spore print sellers numerous “strains” now exist. Unfortunately, much of the history of many of the older strains has been lost, or exist within obfuscated narratives from a variety of websites, with the person/s responsible having disappeared into history. Cailleux and Heim were the first to grow cultures of P. cubensis (as Stropharia cubensis), publishing their methods in 1957. During the late 1960’s and early 1970’s, those with access to scientific literature adapted laboratory techniques for the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., notably R.E. Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Symmetry Design Symbol Graphics Graphic design Mushroom Fungi Moon Lunar phase
Date: 2021-07-24 21:19:36
Caption: Happy full moon #mushroomlovers 🌑🌘🌗🌖🌕🌔🌓🌒🌑 #Repost from @symbiiotica 🍄 How do lunar cycles influence the cycles of fungi? Considering the fact that lunar gravity influences every being on this planet, especially water bodies and those with water-based bodies (most of life), and considering the fact that most mushrooms are > 90% water… it’s almost certain that the moons influences plays SOME role in fungal fruitings, behaviors and expressions. Many Indigenous cultures that have deeply rooted ethnomycological history, especially those of the northern hemisphere in Scandinavia and Siberia, claim that fruitings of ground-dwelling, fleshy macrofungi occur in greater abundance on the full moon. Since the moons gravity pulls the terrestrial tides (ground water) further up to the surface of the soil on full moons and even more so on new moons, it would make sense that lunar events have a direct effect on fruiting of certain species. But for now the exact knowing of these influences stays happily shrouded in mystery. What the moons exact role is in fungal cycles, we just don’t really know. And maybe we’ll never know. And that’s okay. ~ Here is a rendition of the basic life cycle of a basidiomycete mushroom cycling with the lunar phases. From my perspective, I’ve matched the different energetic expressions of the mushroom life cycle with the associated energetic expressions of the lunar cycle. From full; the biggest, boldest, brightest expression of the mature, sporulating fruiting body, to new; the deep, dark inquisitive phase of underground, rhizospheric mycelial navigation, and back again. In the center is the Elder Futhark Norse Rune, Inguz. The Elder Futhark runic alphabet is said to be the most ancient form of the many Indigenous writing systems from my Scandinavian ancestral lineages(s). Inguz or “the God, Ing” is the rune of fertility and new beginnings, marking a new phase of life. Also interpreted as a seed, the birthing of a new idea or life form. The shape also represents a doorway, the portal to the astral planes.

White Bryophyte Fungus Perennial plant Liverworts Moss
Date: 2024-05-31 21:30:36
Caption: ✨𝗜𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘆𝘅’✨ Imaginez un organisme à la croisée des règnes animal et végétal, qui se développe comme une plante mais se déplace comme un animal. C’est 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗺𝘆𝘅𝗮 𝗳𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗮, un myxomycète. Il se présente sous une forme étonnante, rappelant un corail miniature ou de minuscules stalactites. Ses ramifications blanches se développent sur les bois morts, formant des structures délicates et complexes. Ces ramifications, mesurant jusqu’à 4 millimètres de long, arborent une apparence veloutée due à la présence de spores à leur surface. Loin d’être statique, Ceratiomyxa fruticulosa suit un cycle de vie semblable aux autres myxomycètes. Tout commence sous forme de spores microscopiques dispersées dans l’air. Lorsqu’elles atterrissent sur un substrat favorable, généralement du bois mort humide, elles germent et se transforment en cellules amiboïdes flagellées dotées d’une capacité de mouvement étonnante puis fusionnent pour former un plasmodium, une masse visqueuse multinucléée. Le plasmodium se développe en rampant sur le bois, engloutissant les bactéries et les champignons qui lui servent de nourriture. Au bout d’un certain temps, le plasmodium se transforme en structures reproductrices appelées sporanges. Ces sporanges libèrent à leur tour de nouvelles spores, perpétuant ainsi le cycle de vie de cet organisme étonnant. En décomposant le bois mort, il contribue au recyclage des nutriments dans le sol. J’imagine que le temps extrêmement pluvieux de cette année favorise son apparition nettement plus remarquée actuellement que d’habitude. Petal Pink Font Rose family Flower Arranging Floristry Cut flowers Garden roses Floral design Rose Book of Proverbs
Date: 2021-02-01 00:45:31
Caption: You might have read our recent post about the excessive use of damaging pesticides in imported cut flowers, but of almost equal concern is fungicide usage. You see, Ecuador, where many of the roses sold in the US are grown, has high amounts of rainfall and the greenhouses where these flowers are grown are notorious for holding in humidity and creating fungus issues like Botrytis. Botrytis can create spots on a rose, and often won't appear on a rose until after it's left the farm. To prevent these spots from showing up on roses once they hit the retail market and dissuading customers from buying them, foreign growers have developed a worrisome and toxic method of dipping the entire rose into a vat of fungicide, first dunking the bloom, and then the stem. The workers in charge of this job wear respirator masks to avoid inhaling the products, which are then packaged directly into flower sleeves and shipped to the US (no, they are not rinsed off afterward). Of the 37 products that are used as rose dip treatments, 17 of them have been identified by the Pesticide Action Network to be problematic as groundwater pollutants or harmful to humans, toxic to life and the environment. Unfortunately, Valentine's Day, the biggest flower holiday in the US, is also a time when domestic roses are, by and large, dormant in their fields. This means the VAST majority of cut roses purchased during February have been dipped in a toxic blend of fungicides and pesticides. Not exactly the way I'd want to say "I love you!" #flowers #colorado #coloradoflorist #farmerflorist #coloradofarmer #localflowers #pesticides #fungicides #toxicflowers #valentinesdayflowers #valentinesday #denver #denverflorist #roses #importedroses #buyamericangrown #americangrown #supportlocalflowers #supportamericanfarms #buyamericangrown #coloradogrown #freshcutcolorado #coloradoflowers

Herbaceous plant Plant stem Herb Perennial plant Spiderwort
Date: 2022-05-05 16:57:29
Caption: WHITE FLY Are you battling with white fly?? How do you get rid of yours?? Whiteflies are small flying insects that feed on the sap of plants. They are not harmful to humans, but they are a major agricultural pest. In particular, the honeydew they produce can cause the spread of mould on the surface of the plant leaf. Tune in tomorrow and I’ll show you how I get rid of mine. @matabisprayers #whitefly #agriculture #pestcontrol #aphids #horticulture #biocontrol #plants #gardening #pesticides

Date: 2022-06-20 08:47:37
Caption: A critically endangered fungus - Tea-tree Fingers. This colony was only recently discovered by colleagues and is bigger than all the other previously known fruiting bodies combined. And it's the only colony within a National Park. The whacky thing is it feeds on another couple of specific species of fungi, so to conserve this fungus, we must conserve its hosts first. The other colonies are threatened by sand mining activity. #teatreefingers #rememberthewild #wildvictoria #VicOurNature #fungimap #endangered #SaveWesternportWoodlands

Date: 2024-06-03 13:03:14
Caption: 🆔Inosperma erubescens (Inocybe erubescens) 👉🏽Deadly Fibrecap, brick-red tear mushroom 👉🏽Ziegelroter Risspilz 👉🏽变红丝盖伞 (reddening silk top umbrella) 🌟 The brick-red splitting mushroom (Inocybe erubescens) can be found on forest paths, in parks, or in deciduous forests, especially under beech or linden trees on calcareous, nutrient-rich soils. 🌳🍃 The fruit bodies of this mushroom appear from spring/early summer until late autumn. 🌸🍂 🌟 磚紅裂褶菇（Inocybe erubescens）可以在林間小徑、公園或闊葉林中找到，特別是在含鈣、富營養的土壤中的山毛櫸或菩提樹下。🌳🍃 這種蘑菇的子實體從春季/初夏到晚秋出現。🌸🍂 ⚠️ **WARNING:** Inocybe erubescens contains a potentially fatal dose of the toxin muscarine. ⚠️😱 However, its deadly toxicity depends on the amount consumed; a small piece might not cause severe illness, but eating an entire mushroom can be fatal. 🍄☠️ ⚠️ **警告：** 磚紅裂褶菇含有致命劑量的毒素——毒蕈鹼。⚠️😱 然而，其致命毒性取決於攝入量；少量可能不會引起嚴重疾病，但食用整個蘑菇可能致命。🍄☠️ 📚 All mushroom guidebooks and mushroom hunters advise against consuming any members of the Inocybaceae family! ❌🚫 📚 所有的蘑菇指南書和蘑菇獵人都建議不要食用任何Inocybaceae科的成員！❌🚫 Today, when I discovered these Inocybe mushrooms in the village next to some linden trees, I had to lie down on the ground to take pictures and examine them carefully. 📸👀 This was when a car stopped right behind me, and a man got out to ask if everything was okay. 🚗💨 I felt a bit awkward but reassured him that I was fine. 😅 It was heartening to see that people care if someone is spread out on the ground, regardless of the reason. ❤️🙏 今天，當我在村子裡的一些菩提樹旁發現這些裂褶菇時，我不得不躺在地上拍照並仔細檢查它們。📸👀 就在這時，一輛車停在我身後，一位男士下車問我是否一切正常。🚗💨 我感到有點尷尬，但我向他保證我沒事。😅 看到人們關心無論何種原因躺在地上的人，這讓我感到很暖心。❤️🙏 #InocybeErubescens 🍄🌿🕵️‍♂️ I tried some microscopy on this one. 🔬🧬 Image one shows cheilocystidia, and in between the two big cheilocystidia is a basidium with two sterigmata (they look like tiny antennas). 🧫🔍 The second microscopy image shows spores, which are oval to almond-shaped. I used Melzer's reagent to stain the sample. 🧪📸 Oh my, microscopy terminology is really hard! Definitely need to catch up. 😅 In case you know any of the terms in Chinese, please feel free to comment. Cheilozystidia 緣擔孢子囊 Basidia 擔子 Sterigmata 擔梗

It’s been a slow start for us here in northern Victoria with a very dry autumn and we’re jealous of all the fabulous fungi finds elsewhere! However, the odd fungus has been popping up…. and it looks like we’ll manage to sneak in some rain right as autumn turns to winter and then the hunt will really be on! Fascinating fungi fact: This particular species has been used traditionally by both Aboriginal people and New Zealand Māori people as a tinder and for carrying fire as it will smoulder slowly when dry. #parklandsalburywodonga #mcfarlaneshill #alburywodonga #wodonga #walkingtrail #granitewalkingtrail #fungi #fungus #mushroom #whitepunk #fungifacts #mushroomsofinstagram #fungiphotography #fungilove #nature #autumn #mycology

Caption: AUSTROPAXILUS SP. - Graciela Vicente de @recetasysetas nos comparte este ser fascinante, acompañado de una ficha para ayudarnos en la identificación de esta especie. Este ejemplar podría tratarse de Austropaxilus statuum, aunque sin estudios adicionales, no podemos asegurar la especie con certeza. Características: 📸 Ubicación: Chile ⚠️🍽️ Tóxico 🍁 Estación: Otoño 🌿 Hábitat: Bosque nativo 📏 Tamaño: Hongo de tamaño medio, de unos 10-12 cm. Forma: Similar a una copa con el sombrero algo deprimido en la parte central. Color: Cutícula suave de color amarillo dorado con descamaciones más oscuras. Láminas: Muy decurrentes, de color amarillo. Pie: Corto y amarillo. Corte: Su carne enrojece al cortarla. Textura: Fibroso, de olor fenólico y sabor amargo. Esporada: Parda-amarillenta. Confusiones Posibles: Paxilus involutus - Asociado a álamos. Cantharellus cibarius - Comestible europeo que no se encuentra en Chile. 🍴 Comestibilidad: Este hongo es tóxico y provoca graves daños gastrointestinales, por lo que se desaconseja su consumo. Descubre más sobre la diversidad fúngica en nuestra región y aprende a identificar las especies y las mejores recetas fungi con Graciela Vicente. ¡Sigamos explorando el fascinante mundo de los hongos! #reinofungi #setas #hongo #mushroom #nativo #fungi ¿Ya te encontraste con esta especie? Red Fungus Nature Mushroom Ingredient Natural landscape Agaric Orange Close-up Edible mushroom Cochamó Park Penny Bun Mushroom
Date: 2022-11-09 20:43:42
Caption: Amanita muscaria🍄 es una especie cosmopolita que crece en el sur de Chile🇨🇱, principalmente en la zona de Valdivia y sus alrededores, sin embargo se puede encontrar en casi todas las zonas donde existen predios forestales plantados con pino🌲 radiata. El único uso documentado para Amanita muscaria corresponde a la utilización en contexto chamanico. Aunque Amanita muscaria es un hongo cosmopolita solo ha sido utilizado en algunas culturas indígenas de Estados Unidos🇺🇸, Rusia 🇷🇺y Mesoamérica. Actualmente, Amanita muscaria es consumido a baja escala como un alucinógeno 😵‍💫de uso recreativo, en donde no existe un guía o Chaman. Por lo cual resulta en la mayoría de las ocasiones un consumo irresponsable y bastante peligroso. No existe ningún proceso seguro que elimine todas las toxinas en A. muscaria, sin embargo, si se va a consumir se recomienda secarla al sol, pues este proceso disminuye la toxicidad de la muscarina o toxina mata moscas. El secado al sol🌞 también ayuda en la descarboxilación parcial del ácido iboténico, el cual se transforma en muscimol, sustancia que es aproximadamente 10 veces más alucinógeno. La acción farmacológica del muscimol es diferente de la psilocibina (Psilocibes spp. “Cucumelo”), ya que actúa como agonista del receptor GABAa. Los riesgos pueden disminuir más si se consume solo la película roja externa del sombrero y la capa que yace inmediatamente por debajo, en el hongo seco. 🛑NUNCA SE DEBE CONSUMIR FRESCO y siempre acompañado de un cuidador o alguna persona que no consuma. 👉Ante todas las recomendaciones pertinentes, siempre es mejor no consumir Amanita muscaria para su uso recreativo. 🛩️Comparte si te gustó Créditos @mushroom_and_us @vicentevaldesguzmanphotography #amanita #amanitamuscaria #setas #hongos #fungi #reinofungi #fungilover #picfee #fotoverweij #photographersassociates #ig_discover_holland #igholland #dutch_connextion #catch_holland #dutchphotoacademy #thiswaymoments #heelnederland_fotografeert #holland_photolovers #nb_nature_brilliance #vroegevogels_bnnvara

Date: 2024-05-23 17:07:15
Caption: ✅This is a great example of what happens to a crop when it is not sprayed. 🚜The picture shows what happens when a spray miss occurs. 🌾The noticeable yellowing indicates the crop’s deterioration due to diseases such as yellow rust. Why is this a problem ? ☀️ The process of photosynthesis, which is vital for the plant’s growth, relies on the absorption of light into the plant’s green leaves. When these leaves are afflicted by disease, the amount of photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) they can absorb is significantly reduced. This leads to a decrease in photosynthesis, ultimately resulting in a lower yield. ❌This could have occured due to a blocked nozzle. #sprayer #ellieswelly #spraymiss #farmers #farmersmarket #spraying #fungicides #crops #wheat #bread #zyatt #agriculture #sprayermachine #farmerlife #farmerstyle

Caption: Here’s what big ph*rm@ doesn’t want you to know… Mushrooms are revolutionizing modern medicine! From boosting immunity to sharpening your mind, these versatile fungi offer a bounty of health benefits that are hard to ignore. What really makes them game changers are these key ingredients: - Polysaccharides - complex sugars that stimulate the immune system and have been shown to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects. - Beta-glucans - type of soluble fiber that helps regulate the immune system by binding to immune cells and stimulate them to attack invading pathogens, while also reducing inflammation in the body. - Active hexose correlated compound - nutritional product extracted from a variety of mushrooms that is commonly used to prevent and treat cancer. It contains a mixture of the polysaccharides, amino acids and minerals. I have experienced the amazing benefits first hand. My go-tos are @real_mushrooms and @thegeniusbrand. Spring Paint Mural Stock photography
Date: 2024-05-28 11:29:13
Caption: This structure caught my attention as it harmonizes with nature, so I stopped to take a picture of it. I originally thought this was a coffee shop in the middle of a mountain road, away from houses but right in front of a temple. It’s just naturally beautiful in every angle. Later, I found out that it was a wood-ear beverage and sausage shop. The owners were so hospitable and kind to show us their fruiting room. They cultivate the mushroom by themselves and process it into a beverage.  I like wood-ear beverages because they are healthy. Also, it contains substances which are good for our overall health. So I bought three bottles. Besides the beverage, I bought the pink mushroom, which tasted so good when cooked with ginger and seasoned with soy sauce.  #miaoli #miaolitravel #miaolifood #woodearmushrooms #woodear #fungicultura #fungiculture #taiwantravels #taiwanmountain #mountainview #natureshots

Design
Date: 2024-06-02 06:10:48
Caption: 🍄🎞️📽️📷 “Las vidas incontroladas de los hongos son un regalo –y una guía– cuando nos falla el mundo controlado que creíamos tener”. Anna Lowenhaupt Tsing, Los hongos del fin del mundo. Aquí los procesos educativos son espacios de creación lenta. Juntos tratamos de intuir, probar, digerir, girar. A veces no hay avance. Otras el proceso avanza antes que tu propio pensamiento. Antes que tu propia acción. De eso se trata al fin y al cabo. De prestar atención a plena a esos que llamamos otros -hongos, flores, abejas, barro, caliza o talco- y que disponen de estrategias de vida propias de las que poder aprender de y con. En este proceso están implicados Darío Fernández, micólogo, junto con Deneb Martos, educadora y artista audiovisual. Ellos, a partir de una estrategia de pensamiento y creación micélica, están actualmente abriendo distintos caminos de experimentación para lograr hacer visible lo invisible, pensando la fotografía de forma expandida y en relación al ecosistema en el que habitamos. Haciendo uso de herramientas de la ciencia, la foto sin cámara, el cine experimental, el cultivo y sesiones de campo siguen identificando y comprendiendo especies micológicas de nuestro entorno para poder comprender y visibilizar su papel ecológico. . . . #micología #mycology #subsuelo #fotosincamara #cineexperimental #reinofungi #tercermaestro

Date: 2023-11-10 16:00:59
Caption: The brightly-coloured waxcaps are often thought of as the orchids of the fungi kingdom because they are so vibrant and showy, and also quite particular. They will only grow on undisturbed, nutrient-poor grasslands like ancient pasture and other land that has never been ploughed or fertilised. As a result, many species are rare and hard to find but some grow much closer to home – literally. Waxcaps can appear in garden lawns, grassy churchyards and even the occasional cricket pitch as long as the conditions are right. Wherever you find them, their presence means you’re in a very special place. Scarlet Waxcap © Graeme Lyons This image features in our 2024 Wildlife of Sussex Calendar, available from our online shop - see link in bio #Sussex #Waxcap #FungiFriday

Smile Happiness Fines herbes Herb Houseplant Sicilian cuisine Stuffing
Date: 2023-10-22 12:40:07
Caption: Cientistas da Universidade Estadual do Ceará (Uece) criaram um fungicida natural capaz de proteger mais de 500 espécies de plantas, como cajueiro, coqueiro e pé de acerola, contra doenças como a podridão seca (causada pelo Lasiodiplodia theobromae). A descoberta recebeu carta-patente do Instituto Nacional da Propriedade Industrial (INPI). Os próximos passos dos pesquisadores serão para comercializar o produto e para realizar outros testes na avaliação do uso farmacológico da substância. As informações foram divulgadas pela comunicação da Universidade. O fungicida pode proteger plantações inteiras, com baixo custo e de forma natural, o que pode beneficiar muitos que dependem da agricultura familiar para o sustento. Além disso, há possibilidade de uso como medicamento para humanos conforme o estudo avance. Veja mais detalhes em nosso site, acessando o link que está na bio. (Foto: Uece/Reprodução) #fungicida #ciencia #Ceará #DiáriodoNordeste

Fungus Mushroom Orange Agaricomycetes Medicinal mushroom Autumn Bolete Agaricaceae Agaric Edible mushroom
Date: 2020-11-26 03:59:14
Caption: Níscalo – Robellón – Callampa rosada . El género Lactarius comprende casi 600 especies ectomicorrícicas pertenecientes a la familia Russulaceae. Su mayor característica es la segregación de un látex de color que varía según la especie y que tiene apariencia lechosa, cualidad que le da el epíteto a su género, pues Lactarius proviene del latín “lac” que significa “leche”, siendo el ejemplar probablemente más conocido Lactarius deliciosus. . Esta especie se encuentra en plantaciones forestales de Pinus radiata en Chile y su aparición es otoñal e invernal, aunque en ciertas condiciones puede extender incluso hasta verano. Es una seta muy fácil de identificar, a grandes rasgos: tiene una forma de embudo, es quebradizo, con sombrero de color crema a anaranjado, convexo que se aplana con la edad, sobre la superficie del píleo tiene círculos concéntricos; las láminas son adnadas y decurrentes, de color naranjo vivo o zanahoria, al rasgarlas exuda el látex y este se oxida con la presencia de aire dejando un color verdoso; y el pie es cilíndrico, concolor al sombrero, macizo al inicio y luego hueco. . Se trata de una especie muy distintiva por estas características, sin embargo hay otra especie muy parecida en el país: L. quieticolor, que correspondería a la imagen, pues tiene un sombrero mucho más pálido y blanquecino a diferencia de L. deliciosus que tiene el sombrero más anaranjado fuerte y que en apreciación del profesor Gotz es la especie que estaría mayormente en Chile en las plantaciones de pino insigne. . . Lactarius quieticolor Romagn. . . #nature #mushroom #fungi #hongos #seta #fungiworld #mushroomspotting #mycology #fungilove #fungifun #funghi #woods #forest #mycophile #fungus #mushroomlover #fungifreaks #micelium #fantasticfungi #mushroomlove #mushroomhunting #fungo #fungiphotography #mushroomsociety #hongosdechile #lactarius #milkcap

Date: 2024-06-02 06:10:48
Caption: 🍄🎞️📽️📷 “Las vidas incontroladas de los hongos son un regalo –y una guía– cuando nos falla el mundo controlado que creíamos tener”. Anna Lowenhaupt Tsing, Los hongos del fin del mundo. Aquí los procesos educativos son espacios de creación lenta. Juntos tratamos de intuir, probar, digerir, girar. A veces no hay avance. Otras el proceso avanza antes que tu propio pensamiento. Antes que tu propia acción. De eso se trata al fin y al cabo. De prestar atención a plena a esos que llamamos otros -hongos, flores, abejas, barro, caliza o talco- y que disponen de estrategias de vida propias de las que poder aprender de y con. En este proceso están implicados Darío Fernández, micólogo, junto con Deneb Martos, educadora y artista audiovisual. Ellos, a partir de una estrategia de pensamiento y creación micélica, están actualmente abriendo distintos caminos de experimentación para lograr hacer visible lo invisible, pensando la fotografía de forma expandida y en relación al ecosistema en el que habitamos. Haciendo uso de herramientas de la ciencia, la foto sin cámara, el cine experimental, el cultivo y sesiones de campo siguen identificando y comprendiendo especies micológicas de nuestro entorno para poder comprender y visibilizar su papel ecológico. . . . #micología #mycology #subsuelo #fotosincamara #cineexperimental #reinofungi #tercermaestro

Date: 2022-11-09 20:43:42
Caption: Amanita muscaria🍄 es una especie cosmopolita que crece en el sur de Chile🇨🇱, principalmente en la zona de Valdivia y sus alrededores, sin embargo se puede encontrar en casi todas las zonas donde existen predios forestales plantados con pino🌲 radiata. El único uso documentado para Amanita muscaria corresponde a la utilización en contexto chamanico. Aunque Amanita muscaria es un hongo cosmopolita solo ha sido utilizado en algunas culturas indígenas de Estados Unidos🇺🇸, Rusia 🇷🇺y Mesoamérica. Actualmente, Amanita muscaria es consumido a baja escala como un alucinógeno 😵‍💫de uso recreativo, en donde no existe un guía o Chaman. Por lo cual resulta en la mayoría de las ocasiones un consumo irresponsable y bastante peligroso. No existe ningún proceso seguro que elimine todas las toxinas en A. muscaria, sin embargo, si se va a consumir se recomienda secarla al sol, pues este proceso disminuye la toxicidad de la muscarina o toxina mata moscas. El secado al sol🌞 también ayuda en la descarboxilación parcial del ácido iboténico, el cual se transforma en muscimol, sustancia que es aproximadamente 10 veces más alucinógeno. La acción farmacológica del muscimol es diferente de la psilocibina (Psilocibes spp. “Cucumelo”), ya que actúa como agonista del receptor GABAa. Los riesgos pueden disminuir más si se consume solo la película roja externa del sombrero y la capa que yace inmediatamente por debajo, en el hongo seco. 🛑NUNCA SE DEBE CONSUMIR FRESCO y siempre acompañado de un cuidador o alguna persona que no consuma. 👉Ante todas las recomendaciones pertinentes, siempre es mejor no consumir Amanita muscaria para su uso recreativo. 🛩️Comparte si te gustó Créditos @mushroom_and_us @vicentevaldesguzmanphotography #amanita #amanitamuscaria #setas #hongos #fungi #reinofungi #fungilover #picfee #fotoverweij #photographersassociates #ig_discover_holland #igholland #dutch_connextion #catch_holland #dutchphotoacademy #thiswaymoments #heelnederland_fotografeert #holland_photolovers #nb_nature_brilliance #vroegevogels_bnnvara

Date: 2020-11-26 03:59:14
Caption: Níscalo – Robellón – Callampa rosada . El género Lactarius comprende casi 600 especies ectomicorrícicas pertenecientes a la familia Russulaceae. Su mayor característica es la segregación de un látex de color que varía según la especie y que tiene apariencia lechosa, cualidad que le da el epíteto a su género, pues Lactarius proviene del latín “lac” que significa “leche”, siendo el ejemplar probablemente más conocido Lactarius deliciosus. . Esta especie se encuentra en plantaciones forestales de Pinus radiata en Chile y su aparición es otoñal e invernal, aunque en ciertas condiciones puede extender incluso hasta verano. Es una seta muy fácil de identificar, a grandes rasgos: tiene una forma de embudo, es quebradizo, con sombrero de color crema a anaranjado, convexo que se aplana con la edad, sobre la superficie del píleo tiene círculos concéntricos; las láminas son adnadas y decurrentes, de color naranjo vivo o zanahoria, al rasgarlas exuda el látex y este se oxida con la presencia de aire dejando un color verdoso; y el pie es cilíndrico, concolor al sombrero, macizo al inicio y luego hueco. . Se trata de una especie muy distintiva por estas características, sin embargo hay otra especie muy parecida en el país: L. quieticolor, que correspondería a la imagen, pues tiene un sombrero mucho más pálido y blanquecino a diferencia de L. deliciosus que tiene el sombrero más anaranjado fuerte y que en apreciación del profesor Gotz es la especie que estaría mayormente en Chile en las plantaciones de pino insigne. . . Lactarius quieticolor Romagn. . . #nature #mushroom #fungi #hongos #seta #fungiworld #mushroomspotting #mycology #fungilove #fungifun #funghi #woods #forest #mycophile #fungus #mushroomlover #fungifreaks #micelium #fantasticfungi #mushroomlove #mushroomhunting #fungo #fungiphotography #mushroomsociety #hongosdechile #lactarius #milkcap

Advertising Science Marine biology Graphic design Great Pacific Garbage Patch North Pacific Gyre Fungi Plastic Ocean Plastic pollution Waste Garbage patch
Date: 2024-06-05 22:25:18
Caption: Nature is, once again, the MVP.⁠ ⁠ Scientists have found an ocean-borne fungus chomping through plastic trash suspended in the mega-sized garbage patch in the Pacific Ocean.⁠ ⁠ The fungus, named Parengyodontium album, can break down UV-exposed polyethylene, the most pervasive form of plastic waste in our oceans.⁠ ⁠ It's exciting news, but it doesn't mean you can start recklessly going through plastic grocery bags and water bottles. Our new hero can break down a piece of plastic at roughly 0.05 percent per day.⁠ ⁠ It is, however, a reminder of how impressive the world's species are.⁠ ⁠ Read more about plastic-eating fungi at the link in our bio.

Date: 2024-06-05 06:29:31
Caption: Gallacea Scleroderma is one of New Zealand’s varieties of pouch fungi with fleshy, enclosed fruiting bodies. Truffles are ascomycete fungi, but most of these New Zealand pouch fungi are basidiomycetes. The gills are packed tight inside the pouch and they sit in many different genera. . Their spores are thought to be often spread by birds. They are very cool fungi. #fungus #fungi #mycology #fungihunting #newzealandfungi #newzealand #fungiphotography #macrophotography

Road surface Road Vegetation Thoroughfare Hill station Asphalt Lane Overhead power line pole Public utility
Date: 2024-05-28 11:29:13
Caption: This structure caught my attention as it harmonizes with nature, so I stopped to take a picture of it. I originally thought this was a coffee shop in the middle of a mountain road, away from houses but right in front of a temple. It’s just naturally beautiful in every angle. Later, I found out that it was a wood-ear beverage and sausage shop. The owners were so hospitable and kind to show us their fruiting room. They cultivate the mushroom by themselves and process it into a beverage.  I like wood-ear beverages because they are healthy. Also, it contains substances which are good for our overall health. So I bought three bottles. Besides the beverage, I bought the pink mushroom, which tasted so good when cooked with ginger and seasoned with soy sauce.  #miaoli #miaolitravel #miaolifood #woodearmushrooms #woodear #fungicultura #fungiculture #taiwantravels #taiwanmountain #mountainview #natureshots

Caption: 🍄Hongo Sombrero Violeta o Cortinarius Magellanicus Se encuentra en el sur de #Chile y #Argentina, y fructifica entre enero y mayo. Es una especie micorrizógena, que crece cerca de árboles principalmente del género Nothofagus. Como se puede ver en la fotografía su color es violáceo con tintes púrpuras. Este hongo presenta un sombrero de 1 a 8 cm de diámetro. Tanto el sombrero como el estipe están cubiertos de una capa mucilaginosa. La esporada es de color pardo. Font Science
Date: 2024-06-05 22:25:18
Caption: Nature is, once again, the MVP.⁠ ⁠ Scientists have found an ocean-borne fungus chomping through plastic trash suspended in the mega-sized garbage patch in the Pacific Ocean.⁠ ⁠ The fungus, named Parengyodontium album, can break down UV-exposed polyethylene, the most pervasive form of plastic waste in our oceans.⁠ ⁠ It's exciting news, but it doesn't mean you can start recklessly going through plastic grocery bags and water bottles. Our new hero can break down a piece of plastic at roughly 0.05 percent per day.⁠ ⁠ It is, however, a reminder of how impressive the world's species are.⁠ ⁠ Read more about plastic-eating fungi at the link in our bio.

Date: 2023-09-19 13:13:32
Caption: SABÍAS QUÉ? La melena de león, o Hericium erinaceus, es un hongo que se ha utilizado en la medicina tradicional china y japonesa debido a sus posibles beneficios para la salud. Algunos de los beneficios asociados con la melena de león incluyen: 1. Apoyo cognitivo: Se ha sugerido que los compuestos en la melena de león pueden mejorar la función cerebral, incluida la memoria y la concentración. 2. Estimulación del crecimiento de nervios: La melena de león contiene componentes que pueden promover la regeneración de las células nerviosas y ayudar en la salud del sistema nervioso. 3. Propiedades antioxidantes: Los antioxidantes en este hongo pueden ayudar a combatir el estrés oxidativo y proteger las células del daño. 4. Refuerzo del sistema inmunológico: Se ha estudiado si los polisacáridos de la melena de león pueden fortalecer la respuesta inmunológica del cuerpo ante infecciones. 5. Salud digestiva: Algunos informes sugieren que la melena de león puede beneficiar la salud del sistema digestivo y reducir la inflamación gastrointestinal. 6. Potencial para la salud cardiovascular: Aunque la investigación está en curso, se ha explorado si la melena de león podría tener un impacto positivo en la salud del corazón y los niveles de colesterol. #melenadeleon #lionsmanemushroom #fungy #mushrooms #mushroomgourmet #liquidculture #pda #placapetri #fungus #micelio #champiñones #pinkoyster #blueoyster #goldoyster #melenaleon #kingoyster #blackpearlkingoyster #phoenixoyster #italianoyster #indianoyster #djamor #chile # #latam #miceliochile #mundofungi #fungicultura #fungi # #hongosgourmet #colombia #hongoscolombia

Natural material Nail Fungus Plant Fungi Dendrocollybia Chihuahuan Desert
Date: 2022-10-03 11:47:28
Caption: Dendrocollybia racemosa - Branched shanklet Not my find but a collaborative effort to collect and record this rare species. I’m thrilled to get the opportunity to witness this one. The location has been recorded, and pending permissions, a sample will be making its way to Kew Gardens to be included in their genome sequencing projects and the national collection. Found by: Nicky Freeman Collected & record by: Iona Fraser @ashdownforage The species is characterised by its unusual stem, which is covered with short lateral branches. The branches often produce spherical slimeheads of translucent conidiophores  on their swollen tips. The conidiophores produce conidia (asexual spores) by mitosis. Because the fungus can rely on either sexual or asexual modes of reproduction, fruit bodies sometimes have reduced or even missing caps. The unusual stems originate from black pea-sized structures called sclerotia. The anamorphic form of the fungus, known as Tilachlidiopsis racemosa, is missing the sexual stage of its life cycle. It can reproduce at relatively low temperatures, an adaptation believed to improve its ability to grow quickly and fruit on decomposing mushrooms. (Info via Wikimili) #allthingsfungi

Caption: Meet mold—a fascinating form of fungi! Mold plays a crucial role in nature by breaking down and recycling organic material. 🌱 While it’s not something you want on your food or in your home, mold is everywhere, thriving in moist environments and helping decompose everything from fallen leaves to leftovers in your fridge. One of nature’s best recyclers! 🔄♻️ Curious to learn more about how mold works and its role in the ecosystem? Check out the Mold lesson in our ‘Activities for Kids’ in our online resources! Text Font Science
Date: 2024-05-27 15:23:36
Caption: Feast on yeast, the tiny powerhouse responsible for some of your favorite foods and drinks! 🍺☕️ Yeast is a single-celled fungus that can reproduce itself asexually through budding and plays a vital role in the culinary world, especially in baking and brewing. 🍞 These types of fungi work by converting sugars into carbon dioxide and alcohol in a process called fermentation. 🔬 But yeast isn't just for food and drink—it's also crucial in biotechnology for developing medications and environmental efforts to produce biofuels. 💊 💣 There is even a species of yeast that has been studied for its potential ability to work as a bioremediator in TNT-polluted marine environments. 🧐 As you can see, humans have had an intimate relationship with this fungus for thousands of years. 📚 Head to the Yeast lesson in the ‘Activities for Kids’ section of our online curriculum for some fun yeast education exercises! Link in bio. #Yeast #Funglossary #Microbiology #mycology #fungieducation #funga #fungikingdom #activitiesforkids

Orange Fungus
Date: 2024-05-26 11:18:21
Caption: Growing a new fungus is always interesting. This is Cordyceps militaris #cordycepsmilitaris a fungi that until recently was not allowed to be grown here in Australia. Now we can legally grow this, I was curious to give it a go - especially after investing so much time into trying to grow Cordyceps gunnii, unsuccessfully! Not my best grow! And I have been watching lots of US growers really get to dial these in to be an art. But I grew these on white rice with no nutrients to start out so I could get an idea of growth, yield, and other characteristics that may help later! One big hint, don't try to grow these when it is hot without cooling! #guerrillamycology #fungiculture #🍄 #fungi #fungus #funghi #hongos #myceliumrunning #radicalmycology #radmycology #thinkfungi #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #mycelium #mushrooms #myceliumrunning #myceliumnetwork #myceliummood #cordyceps #cordycepsmilitaris #cordycepsgunnii #introducedfungi #notnativefungi #notwildfungi #ethnomycology #entheogenicfungi #fungiphotography #mushroomphotography

Date: 2024-05-28 11:29:13
Caption: This structure caught my attention as it harmonizes with nature, so I stopped to take a picture of it. I originally thought this was a coffee shop in the middle of a mountain road, away from houses but right in front of a temple. It’s just naturally beautiful in every angle. Later, I found out that it was a wood-ear beverage and sausage shop. The owners were so hospitable and kind to show us their fruiting room. They cultivate the mushroom by themselves and process it into a beverage.  I like wood-ear beverages because they are healthy. Also, it contains substances which are good for our overall health. So I bought three bottles. Besides the beverage, I bought the pink mushroom, which tasted so good when cooked with ginger and seasoned with soy sauce.  #miaoli #miaolitravel #miaolifood #woodearmushrooms #woodear #fungicultura #fungiculture #taiwantravels #taiwanmountain #mountainview #natureshots

Caption: Einige Pilzarten kann man zwar kultivieren, nach Samen sucht man für die Anzucht aber vergeblich. Pilze gehören nicht zu den Pflanzen und bilden auch keine Samen. Stattdessen geben die Fruchtkörper sogenannte Sporen in die Umgebung ab, um sich zu vermehren. Graphics
Date: 2024-04-03 15:00:08
Caption: Did you know that improper storage of grains and nuts could result in the production of a potent toxin? Aflatoxin B2 is mainly produced by the fungi Aspergillus flavus. Aflatoxin-producing molds are commonly detected in inadequately stored agricultural produce, including maize, rice, cassava, cottonseed, millet, sorghum, sesame seeds, sweetcorn, chili peppers, tree nuts, sunflower seeds, spices, and wheat. Aflatoxin B2, while not as toxic as Aflatoxin B1, can affect children, leading to delays in development and stunted growth. Prolonged exposure has also been linked to liver cancer and liver impairment. #sigmaaldrich #chemistry #chemicals #moleculeoftheday #science #laboratory #supelco #32755 #fungi #fungifacts #naturalproducts

Font Graphic design Publication
Date: 2024-06-04 20:45:21
Caption: Este hongo, del género Clavaria, observado en la Quebrada de los Cuervos (Treinta y Tres) por m_coronel94, ¡es nuestra Observación del Mes en NaturalistaUY! - Los hongos pertenecen al Reino Fungi y son unos de los seres vivos más diversos de nuestro planeta. Algunos de ellos, como esta Clavaria, se alimentan de la hojarasca y materia orgánica que descomponen en los bosques. Por eso decimos que juegan un rol muy importante en el ciclado de nutrientes de los ecosistemas. Este grupo de hongos está formado por dos partes: el micelio, que crece en el sustrato, y el cuerpo fructífero, que crece en época reproductiva y normalmente podemos observar a simple vista. En el grupo de las Clavaria en particular, su forma recuerda a los corales, y por ello les llamamos “hongos coraloides”. Si bien los hongos crecen durante todo el año, en nuestro país es en otoño cuando encuentran mejores condiciones de humedad y temperatura para fructificar en mayor cantidad. Aún sabemos muy poco de este Reino. De hecho, menos del 20% de las observaciones de hongos logran ser identificadas a nivel de especie en NaturalistaUY. Para seguir construyendo conocimiento sobre nuestra biodiversidad, ¡sumate vos también a registrar tu entorno! Y si conocés de hongos, ¡ayúdanos con tus identificaciones! - Más detalles en https://www.naturalista.uy/observations/213830990 #reinofungi #coralfungi #Clavariaceae #mushroomidentification #mushroomobserver #observaciondelmesnaturalistauy

Text Font Graphic design Publication endemico.org
Date: 2024-05-29 20:56:52
Caption: Glosario para el Antropoceno | Funga Otoño es temporada de hongos. En esta época es posible observar su estructura macroscópica, que no es más que su cuerpo reproductivo. Es por esta razón que hemos hecho un glosario especial para este reino, tan importante en el engranaje de la vida. Hasta el siglo pasado, se los consideraba como parte del reino Plantae. Sin embargo, estos se acercan más a los animales que a las plantas, aunque no encajan en ninguno de los dos reinos. Los hongos son la base de la vida, pues construyen los puentes entre todos los ciclos biológicos. Así por ejemplo: son los que contribuyen a hacer el reciclaje de nutrientes en la naturaleza, con sus micorrizas son protagonistas de las asociaciones interespecie y el intercambio de nutrientes, muchos tienen un valor gastronómico relevante y otros, incluso son importantes enteógenos, que nos ayudan a elevar nuestro estado de conciencia. Alimentos, medicinas, transformadores de la materia, mágicos habitantes de los bosques y otros tantos ecosistemas, los hongos merecen su espacio en la clasificación de la biodiversidad. La incorporación del término Funga nos invita, entonces, a apreciar y proteger el mundo de estos seres únicos. 🍄 Si te gusta este contenido, te invitamos a guardar, compartir y darle me gusta. Encuentra más gráficas similares en endemico.org/visuales #revistaendemico #funga #reinofungi #hongos #micorrizas #hifas #florafaunayfungi #visualesendemico

Así por ejemplo: son los que contribuyen a hacer el reciclaje de nutrientes en la naturaleza, con sus micorrizas son protagonistas de las asociaciones interespecie y el intercambio de nutrientes, muchos tienen un valor gastronómico relevante y otros, incluso son importantes enteógenos, que nos ayudan a elevar nuestro estado de conciencia. Alimentos, medicinas, transformadores de la materia, mágicos habitantes de los bosques y otros tantos ecosistemas, los hongos merecen su espacio en la clasificación de la biodiversidad. La incorporación del término Funga nos invita, entonces, a apreciar y proteger el mundo de estos seres únicos. 🍄 Si te gusta este contenido, te invitamos a guardar, compartir y darle me gusta. Encuentra más gráficas similares en endemico.org/visuales #revistaendemico #funga #reinofungi #hongos #micorrizas #hifas #florafaunayfungi #visualesendemico

Screenshot Herb Fungicide Fungi Biology Plant
Date: 2024-03-04 23:13:19
Caption: Os fungicidas sítio-específicos, bem como diz o nome, possuem apenas um local de ação no fungo. Esses locais podem ser a síntese de membrana, ou respiração complexo II, ou respiração complexo III, ou síntese de tubulina do fungo. Ex: Triazóis, estrobilurinas, carboxamidas e benzimidazois. Nos fungicidas sítio-específicos, o fungo pode sofrer mutação no sítio bioquímico (o sítio-alvo do fungicida), podendo resultar em uma linhagem resistente. Se tal linhagem resistente ocorrer, a aplicação repetida desses fungicidas pode levar ao aumento de uma subpopulação do patógeno resistente. Multissitios interferem com muitos processos metabólicos de um fungo e são normalmente fungicidas protetores. Uma vez absorvido pela célula do fungo esses fungicidas agem sobre processos como a atividade enzimática que desorganiza numerosas funções celulares. Ex: Mancozebe, Manebe, Tiram, Metiram, Propinebe, Zinebe, Ziram, Clorotalonil, compostos estanhados, sulfúricos, cúpricos, entre outros. Confira as diferenças entre essas classes de fungicidas nesse post! #fungicidas #agropos #agro #agroporamor #agronomo #tecnicoagricola

Labels:
Natural material Fungus
Date: 2024-05-31 21:30:36
Caption: ✨𝗜𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘆𝘅’✨ Imaginez un organisme à la croisée des règnes animal et végétal, qui se développe comme une plante mais se déplace comme un animal. C’est 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗺𝘆𝘅𝗮 𝗳𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗮, un myxomycète. Il se présente sous une forme étonnante, rappelant un corail miniature ou de minuscules stalactites. Ses ramifications blanches se développent sur les bois morts, formant des structures délicates et complexes. Ces ramifications, mesurant jusqu’à 4 millimètres de long, arborent une apparence veloutée due à la présence de spores à leur surface. Loin d’être statique, Ceratiomyxa fruticulosa suit un cycle de vie semblable aux autres myxomycètes. Tout commence sous forme de spores microscopiques dispersées dans l’air. Lorsqu’elles atterrissent sur un substrat favorable, généralement du bois mort humide, elles germent et se transforment en cellules amiboïdes flagellées dotées d’une capacité de mouvement étonnante puis fusionnent pour former un plasmodium, une masse visqueuse multinucléée. Le plasmodium se développe en rampant sur le bois, engloutissant les bactéries et les champignons qui lui servent de nourriture. Au bout d’un certain temps, le plasmodium se transforme en structures reproductrices appelées sporanges. Ces sporanges libèrent à leur tour de nouvelles spores, perpétuant ainsi le cycle de vie de cet organisme étonnant. En décomposant le bois mort, il contribue au recyclage des nutriments dans le sol. J’imagine que le temps extrêmement pluvieux de cette année favorise son apparition nettement plus remarquée actuellement que d’habitude. (Photos en studio 😀) #funghi#champignons#mushrooms#pilze#foret#forest#forestlover#fungis #nature#naturelovers#macronature#beautyofnature #nature#naturalists#biodiversity#naturalistes#wildlife #guidenature #mycologue#mycologie#mycology #photo#photooftheday#picoftheday#natureart #beautyfull#myxomycetes #inthemyxs

Caption: Growing a new fungus is always interesting. This is Cordyceps militaris #cordycepsmilitaris a fungi that until recently was not allowed to be grown here in Australia. Now we can legally grow this, I was curious to give it a go - especially after investing so much time into trying to grow Cordyceps gunnii, unsuccessfully! Not my best grow! And I have been watching lots of US growers really get to dial these in to be an art. But I grew these on white rice with no nutrients to start out so I could get an idea of growth, yield, and other characteristics that may help later! Yellow Fungus Sensitive plant Dog vomit slime mold Slime mold Mold
Date: 2023-06-04 12:16:17
Caption: The brightest spot in the woods, dog vomit slime mold (Fuligo septica ) Like many slime molds, the cells of this species typically aggregate to form a plasmodium, a multinucleate mass of undifferentiated cells that may move in an ameboid-like fashion during the search for nutrients. F. septica's plasmodium may be anywhere from white to yellow-gray This one was so nice and fresh. I was able to do a 20 minute time lapse and compress it down into a few seconds Swipe ➡️to see the pulsating of the slime mold. Early mornings are the best time to observe this slime mold. This was spotted on a Ash log, but in urban areas, often found on mulch and wood chip piles. . . #slimemoldsunday #slimemouldsunday #slimemouldsofinstagram #slimemold # #slimemould #dogvomitslimemold #fuligoseptica #yellowslimemold #mycetozoa #slemsvamp #intheforest #hikingfinds #mushroomhunter #trollsmör #scrambledeggslime #flowersoftan #simplenaturefinds #mushroomsofpennsylvania #fungioftheday #naturelovers #fungifreaks #fantasticfungus #forestfinds #nuts_about_nature

Happiness
Date: 2021-01-04 13:01:19
Caption: We must not continue down this path of indiscriminate war on microbes. 🔬 The soil microbes, and the beneficial microbes of our body, are the foundation of all life. In our misunderstanding and fear of specific microbes, we have launched an all out war on Nature. Bacteria, fungi, and viruses are critical to life on Earth. Antibiotics, pesticides and fungicides, sanitizers, etc are being used so injudiciously, that the very fabric of human and planetary health is at stake. We must learn the patience to discover the difference between friend and foe. As with all things in Nature, diversity is the key. Without diversity, the system collapses. The invisible microbes do not have a voice of their own - at least not in the traditional sense. But if we continue to ignore them, the microbial ecosystem will become so imbalanced that we will be forced to pay attention to their power. There is no life in a fully sterilized world. We must learn to live alongside these microbes, and acknowledge the significant role they play in the health of our planet. #microbes #invisible #tiny #microscopic #soilorganisms #organism #life #earth #motherearth #ecosystem #circleoflife #systemsthinking #systems #fungicides #pesticides

Caption: Finalmente aderi ao queridinho das “blogueres de casa” 🤣 O #lysoform Bruto Original (têm outros tipos tbm) é um desinfetante de uso geral, funcionando como: #germicida #bactericida #fungicida. . . . . Esse produto é indicado para uso em limpeza de latas, lixeiras, pias e ralos, uma vez que possui capacidade de eliminar bactérias e germes. Dessa forma a limpeza é feita de forma que o mau cheiro seja eliminado e o ambiente limpo, esse tipo de produto não pode entrar em contato com o corpo humano. . . Ele também pode ser usado na limpeza de ambientes e superfícies laváveis como pisos e azulejos, podendo ser aplicado também nas paredes internas e bordas do vaso sanitário. Outra opção de uso de produto é na limpeza das roupas, usando apenas durante o enxague. . . Quando usado na forma pura o produto age como bactericida, podendo ser usado para desinfetar paredes, armários, maçanetas, entre outras coisas que não são levadas à boca. O indicado é aplicar e deixar agir por dez minutos, outra dica é colocar o produto em uma pequena área do local que deseja aplicar para se certificar de que não irá causar manchas ou danificar o objeto ou local. . . Um alerta do fabricante é que esse produto não pode ser usado por mulheres grávidas 🤰🏻, pois ele possui em sua fórmula o benzeno, substância que pode ocasionar algum tipo de má formação no feto. MODO DE USO: . . Para desodorização diluir um copo (250 Ml) em 10 litros de água. Para lavar roupas use ½ copo (125 Ml) no processo final da lavagem. Não precisa enxaguar. Para desinfecção use o produto puro. Tempo de contato: 10 Minutos. . . Tbm pode ser usado na limpeza de estofado, colchão; para facilitar o uso nesses casos coloque dentro de um borrifador. Essa dica aqui aprendi com a Rê @duplex401 👍🏼 . . . . . Gostaram? Bora compartilhar com #azamigas pq #dicaboaédicacompartilhada 😁🙋🏻‍♀️ . . . . . . . #eaímeupovo #cmldicas . Caption: Growing your own shiitake mushrooms on logs in your garden is surprisingly easy. You inoculate some wood, wait a year or two (yes, it does require a bit of patience) and then, one rainy day, you get a harvest of homegrown shiitakes! And then more and more from those same logs each year, for about the next five years.⁠ ⁠ Once you get into the swing of it, you can inoculate a few additional logs each autumn - ensuring a never-ending harvest and thus plenty of big warming bowls of mushroom ramen and stir-fried shiitake and everything delicious and wonderful.⁠ ⁠ So, want to know exactly what we mean by 'inoculate logs'?⁠ ⁠ At the link in our bio, we have a free Getting Started With Mushroom Cultivation guide, which includes a section on how to grow shiitake on logs. It'll help get your head around the basics, including:⁠ 🪵 What supplies you need.⁠ 🪵 How to prepare your substrate.⁠ 🪵 Inoculation and incubation.⁠ 🪵 And a little trick we learned to help bring on fruiting.⁠ ⁠ Alrighty, lovely - go download your guide, have a read and then let us know if you have any questions? We're always here to help. Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Red Petal Garden roses Pink Cut flowers Flower bouquet Flower Arranging Valentine's Day Love Rose family Flower bouquet Rose Flower Valentine's Day Valentines Day Bouquet Garden roses Floral design Floristry
Date: 2023-02-14 09:09:26
Caption: #SanValentino è sinonimo di baci, cioccolatini ma soprattutto… #fiori! Immancabili le #rose, simbolo di #passione per eccellenza. Ma vale la pena fare regalarle alla persona amata? La risposta – nella maggior parte dei casi – è no. O almeno se si vuole fare un bel regalo all’#ambiente. In vista di questa celebrazione, infatti, tonnellate di rose refrigerate vengono trasportate da Paesi del Sud America e dell’Africa orientale all’Europa, dove vengono poi vendute spesso a caro prezzo. Ma dietro la bellezza di questi fiori si nascondono veri e propri cocktail di #pesticidi, comprese quelle certificate Fairtrade. A svelare il lato oscuro delle rose è la recente analisi condotta dalla rivista tedesca Öko-Test. In totale sono stati 21 i #mazzidirose esaminati, venduti da note aziende leader nella consegna dei fiori come Fleurop e Euroflorist. E il numero di diversi pesticidi rilevati è impressionante: ben 54. Oltre 3/4 dei boquet hanno riportato dei punteggi scarsi o insufficienti, inclusi quelli molto costosi. I prezzi sono molto variabili: vanno da 1,99 euro per dodici rose a 39,95 euro per otto rose. Fra le sostanze rilevate vi sono anche fitofarmaci potenzialmente cancerogeni, mutageni, reprotossici e tossici per le api. Ma non finisce qua. Su 3/4 dei mezzi di fiori analizzati è stato spruzzato uno spray a base di #insetticida Thiacloprid e di #fungicida Carbendazim, messi al bando in Europa. Secondo l’Agenzia europea per le sostanze chimiche (ECHA), questa sostanze sono potenzialmente cangerogene e possono influenzare la fertilità e provocare danni nei nascituri. Quando si parla di rose, c’è un altro fattore da considerare oltre alla spinosa questione dei pesticidi: ovvero lo #sfruttamentodeilavoratori. Nella maggior parte dei casi le rose arrivano da Paesi africani come il Kenya, fino al 70% di quelli presenti sul mercato europeo. Qui migliaia di lavoratori sono costretti a turni pesanti per paghe da fame e le donne, in molti casi, sono vittime di molestie sessuali. Gran parte delle rose vendute negli Usa e in Europa arriva anche dalla Colombia e dall’Ecuador, Paesi in cui lo sfruttamento minorile è molto radicato. . . #greenme #greenmeitalia

Caption: 🍄 This month the Spiritual Ecology Study Club gathers once again. Priya Subberwal leads a community discussion around fungal associates. If you’re a lover of mushrooms, and like us, find much fertile ground for learning and turning from fungal metaphors, join us on the session this week by becoming an advaya member (unlock this with a 7-day free trial!) Taking a leaf out of Anna Tsing’s book (somewhat literally), we will think with a politics of impurity and contamination, via our encounters. If we all carry a history of contamination, and purity is not an option, how do we make and re-make the world? What do fungal associates teach us in this respect, about radical movement building, non-linearity, decentralisation and emergence?

Date: 2024-05-31 19:29:17
Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espécie é um saprófito ou parasita específico de espécies do género Betula. Pode observar-se em troncos e ramos, árvores mortas, mas por vezes também em espécimes vivos, provavelmente aproveitando árvores já em mau estado fitossanitário em que a infeção é mais fácil de propagar. Como outros fungos de podridão castanha degrada a parte dos hidratos de carbono(celulose) da lignocelulose, deixando a lignina na forma de fragmentos cúbicos castanhos, em contraste com os fungos de podridão branca que degradam na forma oposta. Em Portugal só encontrei esta espécie em habitats de altitude em serras. Serra da Arada 05/2024 #fomitopsisbetulina #birchpolypore #fomitopsis #fomitopsidaceae #polyporales #polyporaceae #betula #betulapubescens #betulaceltiberica #agaricomycetes #basidiomycota #polypore #fungi #fungus #fungos #fungiphotography #fungiidentification #mushroomidentification #mushroom #mushrooms #mushroomhunting #mushroomphotography #mycophotography #mycology #micologia #cogumelos #cogumelo #wildlifephotography #wildlifephotography

Wood Fungus Trunk Polyporales Mushroom Forest Medicinal mushroom Inonotus Old-growth forest Jungle
Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Date: 2024-05-25 00:31:01
Caption: Hoy tuvimos un entretenido taller de introducción al grabado, en el marco del calendario de otoño de @fungifest 🍄 Revisamos elementos introductorios del grabado, distintos tamaños y materiales para matrices, pasando por la ilustración y grabado, para terminar con la impresión manual con cuchara de palo 🔥 Cómo el tema era relacionado al reino fungi, cada asistente se lanzó en la elaboración de su gráfica para explorar el estampado en papel. Gracias a extensión de la UACh que me facilito en convenio el espacio (donde se vienen otras actividades más este año) y a FungiFest que integró esta mediación en el calendario de sus actividades, estoy muy agradecido tras esta semana modo fungi 🍄 ———— Y con esta actividad, finaliza mi periodo de otoño con lo que tenía planificado de marzo a la fecha. Partió con el desarrollo de las gráficas, un viaje a Santiago, luego Pucón, para terminar en Valdivia compartiendo en itinerancia la serie “Esporada Gráfica”, que el fin de semana pasado monté en el festival como parte de un proceso creativo de grabado. De que estuvo weno, lo estuvo 🍄👀 Bacán la gente que conocí y con quienes compartimos espacios gráficos, espero nos veamos pronto por acá o por allá. Porque el grabado se defiende desde el grabado, a preparar lo de septiembre y de cabeza en los soportes, ya les cuento de eso 🙂 #grabado #fungifest #tallerdegrabado #linografia #linocut #mushrooms🍄

Date: 2024-05-25 00:31:01
Caption: Hoy tuvimos un entretenido taller de introducción al grabado, en el marco del calendario de otoño de @fungifest 🍄 Revisamos elementos introductorios del grabado, distintos tamaños y materiales para matrices, pasando por la ilustración y grabado, para terminar con la impresión manual con cuchara de palo 🔥 Cómo el tema era relacionado al reino fungi, cada asistente se lanzó en la elaboración de su gráfica para explorar el estampado en papel. Gracias a extensión de la UACh que me facilito en convenio el espacio (donde se vienen otras actividades más este año) y a FungiFest que integró esta mediación en el calendario de sus actividades, estoy muy agradecido tras esta semana modo fungi 🍄 ———— Y con esta actividad, finaliza mi periodo de otoño con lo que tenía planificado de marzo a la fecha. Partió con el desarrollo de las gráficas, un viaje a Santiago, luego Pucón, para terminar en Valdivia compartiendo en itinerancia la serie “Esporada Gráfica”, que el fin de semana pasado monté en el festival como parte de un proceso creativo de grabado. De que estuvo weno, lo estuvo 🍄👀 Bacán la gente que conocí y con quienes compartimos espacios gráficos, espero nos veamos pronto por acá o por allá. Porque el grabado se defiende desde el grabado, a preparar lo de septiembre y de cabeza en los soportes, ya les cuento de eso 🙂 #grabado #fungifest #tallerdegrabado #linografia #linocut #mushrooms🍄

Garden Dome Dome Cob Hut Mushroom House Aesthetics
Date: 2021-09-17 17:59:24
Caption: The Future is Fungal 🍄 Fungi fashion? Fungi furniture? Fungi foundations? 🧐 Not only is this attractive alliteration, but it just might be the future of fungi. With its ability to grow rapidly, fit any form, and carry a carbon-neutral footprint, mycelium makes the perfect building material for companies eyeing a more sustainable future. 💫 Mycelium leather has already caught the eyes of industry giants like Adidas, Lululemon, and Stella McCartney. Chairs, canoes, and entire structures have been constructed from fungi. It’s also being used as a replacement for Styrofoam in packaging – eliminating one of the worst environmental pollutants we have. 🙌 Fungi have served as the building blocks for life on Earth for millennia and now we are discovering its immense potential to integrate them to design for our human habitats. The best part is that this is a mutually beneficial relationship for both modern civilization and the natural world. Because mycelium grows agricultural waste the inputs are abundant and dirt cheap, making it an extremely economically viable process. This is only the beginning of the ‘shroom-boom’! 💥 Check out our friends at @soma.eco to discover the latest in mycelial technology! Leave a comment below and tell us what products you’d like to see made of mycelium 🍄 Repost from @xander.softie .⠀⠀ .⠀⠀ .⠀⠀ #mushrooms #mushroom #fungi #fungiacademy  #fungifanatic #fungilove #fantasticfungi #fungusamongus⠀⠀ #mushroomseason #mushroomsociety #mushroomgrowers #mycology #mycoschool #mushrooms_of_our_world #mushaf #mushies #mushlove #magicoffungi #fungimagic #sacredmushrooms #growmushrooms #growfood #growmedicine #mushroomcultivation #cultivatemushrooms #fungifuture #futureisfungi

Caption: Aquele post para salvar📌 Os fungicidas desempenham um papel crucial no manejo dos fungos, responsáveis por aproximadamente 65% das enfermidades que afetam as plantações agrícolas. É fundamental compreender suas categorias para planejar sua aplicação de forma eficaz, prevenindo, por exemplo, o desenvolvimento de resistência a pesticidas. Podemos utilizar pelo menos 8 critérios distintos para classificar os fungicidas agrícolas, a saber: Grupo químico Principio de controle Mobilidade Espectro de ação Mecanismo de ação Potencial de periculosidade ambiental Toxicologia Formulações Quer liberar o seu acesso ao combo de fitopatologia com 52 mapas mentais da matéria? Labels:
Natural material Bryophyte Frost Liverworts
Date: 2024-05-31 21:30:36
Caption: ✨𝗜𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘆𝘅’✨ Imaginez un organisme à la croisée des règnes animal et végétal, qui se développe comme une plante mais se déplace comme un animal. C’est 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗺𝘆𝘅𝗮 𝗳𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗮, un myxomycète. Il se présente sous une forme étonnante, rappelant un corail miniature ou de minuscules stalactites. Ses ramifications blanches se développent sur les bois morts, formant des structures délicates et complexes. Ces ramifications, mesurant jusqu’à 4 millimètres de long, arborent une apparence veloutée due à la présence de spores à leur surface. Loin d’être statique, Ceratiomyxa fruticulosa suit un cycle de vie semblable aux autres myxomycètes. Tout commence sous forme de spores microscopiques dispersées dans l’air. Lorsqu’elles atterrissent sur un substrat favorable, généralement du bois mort humide, elles germent et se transforment en cellules amiboïdes flagellées dotées d’une capacité de mouvement étonnante puis fusionnent pour former un plasmodium, une masse visqueuse multinucléée. Le plasmodium se développe en rampant sur le bois, engloutissant les bactéries et les champignons qui lui servent de nourriture. Au bout d’un certain temps, le plasmodium se transforme en structures reproductrices appelées sporanges. Ces sporanges libèrent à leur tour de nouvelles spores, perpétuant ainsi le cycle de vie de cet organisme étonnant. En décomposant le bois mort, il contribue au recyclage des nutriments dans le sol. J’imagine que le temps extrêmement pluvieux de cette année favorise son apparition nettement plus remarquée actuellement que d’habitude. (Photos en studio 😀) #funghi#champignons#mushrooms#pilze#foret#forest#forestlover#fungis #nature#naturelovers#macronature#beautyofnature #nature#naturalists#biodiversity#naturalistes#wildlife #guidenature #mycologue#mycologie#mycology #photo#photooftheday#picoftheday#natureart #beautyfull#myxomycetes #inthemyxs

Green Red Fungus Mushroom Ingredient Agaric Close-up Bolete Edible mushroom Medicinal mushroom Penny Bun Russula integra Mushroom Agaric
Date: 2024-04-27 01:46:10
Caption: No son plantas, tampoco animales, entonces... ¿Qué son? 🤔🍄 Las setas o callampas que solemos ver en otoño, de diversas formas, tamaños y colores son la parte exterior de algunos hongos que viven bajo tierra o dentro de la materia orgánica en descomposición 🦠🍄 Los hongos son uno de los cinco reinos en que se agrupan a los seres vivos y, por lo tanto, no se consideran ni plantas, ni animales 🍄 No son vegetales, pues no realizan fotosíntesis. Tampoco son animales, pues no ingieren su alimento, lo absorben y sus células tienen pared celular 🧬🍄 Debido a estas razones estos organismos están situados en su propio reino biológico llamado Fungi 🍄 Está es solo una de las muchas curiosidades que podemos aprender sobre estos importantes y lindos seres vivos 🥹🍄 Aprovecho que es otoño temporada donde los vemos por todas partes, así iré enseñando fotitos y videos de las variedades que encontré por estos lados, y por supuesto otras curiosidades sobre ellos 🍄🍄 Recuerda darle amor a este post 💚 #hongo #otoño #hongos #fungi #vidafungi #fungilove #naturaleza #plantas #lamacetitachile #fungichile #valdivia #amanita #amanitas

Caption: ¡Prepárate para el evento fungi del año en Temuco y Padre las Casas! 🎉 El "Funga Festival Temuco y Padre las Casas" se celebrará los días 15 y 16 de junio en el Centro Cultural Padre las Casas (Maquehue #1441). Este festival único busca generar un impacto social significativo, contribuyendo al desarrollo económico, turístico y cultural de nuestra comunidad. Descubre el fascinante mundo de los hongos a través de excursiones, charlas, música, arte y una feria con productos relacionados, desde diseño y textil hasta gastronomía gourmet. Este evento destaca la importancia de los festivales científicos y la música Underground, con un potente line-up musical que no te puedes perder. Mason jar Food storage containers Lid Cookie jar Science Magic Mushroom Cultivation Fungi Mycologist
Date: 2023-12-26 08:09:47
Caption: "Magic Mushroom Cultivation” by Steven Pollock M.D. (1977) is one of the legendary texts in the cultivation of "magic mushrooms". Many popular books were published in the US during the 70’s about the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., but this one stands out as one of the better known, particularly because in time Pollock was (incorrectly) associated with the cubensis strain "P envy". Pollock is also well known for finding and cultivating P. tampanensis, aka "Philosophers Stones". Psilocybe cubensis is one of the most cultivated mushrooms, and as a consequence of extensive collection, cultivation, breeding, and marketing ploys by various spore print sellers numerous “strains” now exist. Unfortunately, much of the history of many of the older strains has been lost, or exist within obfuscated narratives from a variety of websites, with the person/s responsible having disappeared into history. Cailleux and Heim were the first to grow cultures of P. cubensis (as Stropharia cubensis), publishing their methods in 1957. During the late 1960’s and early 1970’s, those with access to scientific literature adapted laboratory techniques for the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., notably R.E. Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Date: 2024-05-30 01:48:21
Caption: Have you seen any fungi in our local parks and reserves? It’s been a slow start for us here in northern Victoria with a very dry autumn and we’re jealous of all the fabulous fungi finds elsewhere! However, the odd fungus has been popping up…. and it looks like we’ll manage to sneak in some rain right as autumn turns to winter and then the hunt will really be on! This specimen of ‘white punk’ (Laetiporus portentosus) was found growing on a stringybark on the Granite Walking Trail (McFarlanes Hill) yesterday. You can see the pores on the underside. Fascinating fungi fact: This particular species has been used traditionally by both Aboriginal people and New Zealand Māori people as a tinder and for carrying fire as it will smoulder slowly when dry. #parklandsalburywodonga #mcfarlaneshill #alburywodonga #wodonga #walkingtrail #granitewalkingtrail #fungi #fungus #mushroom #whitepunk #fungifacts #mushroomsofinstagram #fungiphotography #fungilove #nature #autumn #mycology
